Zoe Caldwell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zoe_Caldwell 0 Zoe Caldwell, OBE (born Ada Caldwell, 14 September 1933) is an Australian actress. She is a four-time Tony Award winner, winning Best Featured Actress in a Play for Slapstick Tragedy (1966), and Best Actress in a Play for The Prime of Miss Jean Brodie (1968), Medea (1982), and Master Class (1996). Her film appearances include The Purple Rose of Cairo (1985), Birth (2004), and Extremely Loud Incredibly Close (2011). She is also the voice of the Grand Councilwoman in the Lilo Stitch franchise.
